{{Infobox website |name = Aviation Safety Network |url = http://aviation-safety.net/ |type = [[Database]] |language = [[English language|English]], [[French language|French]], [[German language|German]], [[Spanish language|Spanish]], [[Dutch language|Dutch]] |owner = Flight Safety Foundation |author = Harro Ranter, Fabian Lujan<ref name=about /> |launch date = January 1996 |alexa = {{DecreasePositive}} 71,698 ({{as of|2014|4|1|alt=April 2014}})<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.alexa.com/siteinfo/aviation-safety.net|title=aviation-safety.net Traffic Statistics|publisher=[[Alexa Internet]]|accessdate= 2017-06-29}}</ref> |current status = Active }}
The '''Aviation Safety Network''' ('''ASN''') is a [[website]] that keeps track of [[Aviation accidents and incidents|aviation accidents, incidents]], and [[Aircraft hijacking|hijackings]]. Their database contains details of over 10,700 reports. The ASN includes an aviation database with aviation investigations, news, photos, and statistics.<ref name=about />
==See also== * [[SAFO]], Safety Alert for Operators
