{{Italic title}}
{{Distinguish|Chronicon Venetum (1388)}}
The '''''Chronicon Venetum et Gradense''''', formerly known as the '''''Chronicon Sagornini''''', is a [[Republic of Venice|Venetian]] chronicle compiled by [[John the Deacon (Venetian chronicler)|John the Deacon]] in ca. 1008. It is the oldest chronicle of the Republic of Venice.{{sfn|Herbermann|1950}} John was the chaplain and perhaps a relative of Venetian Doge [[Pietro II Orseolo]] (r. 991–1009).{{sfn|Herbermann|1950}} The first part, dealing with early history, is lacking, only later becoming more accurate, and in the time of John himself deemed particularly valuable.{{sfn|Herbermann|1950}} It details the reign of Pietro II.{{sfn|Herbermann|1950}}

