enbury'' | [[Siderite]] | [[Australia]] | 1922 | {{convert|2,000|kg|lb|abbr=on}} | <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.museunacional.ufrj.br/dir/exposicoes/geologia/geo015.html|title=Henbury|publisher=National Museum of Brazil|accessdate=4 September 2018 |language=pt}}</ref> |- | | ''Krasnojarsk'' | [[Pallasite]] | [[Russia]] | 1749 | {{convert|700|kg|lb|abbr=on}} | <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.museunacional.ufrj.br/dir/exposicoes/geologia/geo016.html|title=Krasnojarsk|publisher=National Museum of Brazil|accessdate=4 September 2018 |language=pt}}</ref> |- | [[File:Meteorito Pará de Minas 01.jpg|100px]] | ''Pará de Minas'' | [[Siderite]] | [[Minas Gerais]], Brazil | 1934 | {{convert|112|kg|lb|abbr=on}} | |- | [[File:Meteorito Patos de Minas MN 01.jpg|100px]] | ''[[Patos de Minas (meteorite)|Patos de Minas]]'' | [[Octahedrite]] | Minas Gerais, Brazil | 1925 | {{convert|218.4|kg|lb|abbr=on}} | Composed of iron and nickel.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.museunacional.ufrj.br/dir/exposicoes/geologia/geo017.html|title=Meteorito|publisher=National Museum of Brazil|accessdate=4 September 2018 |language=pt}}</ref> |- | [[File:Meteorito Pirapora MN 01.jpg|100px]] | ''Pirapora'' | [[Siderite]] | [[Minas Gerais]], Brazil | 1888 | {{convert|6.18|kg|lb|abbr=on}} | Composed of iron and nickel.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.museunacional.ufrj.br/dir/exposicoes/geologia/geo020.html|title=Pirapora|publisher=National Museum of Brazil|accessdate=4 September 2018 |language=pt}}</ref> |- | | ''Santa Catharina'' | [[Siderite]] | [[Santa Catarina (state)|Santa Catarina]], Brazil | 1875 | {{convert|7,000|kg|lb|abbr=on}} | <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.museunacional.ufrj.br/dir/exposicoes/geologia/geo021.html|title=Santa Catarina|publisher=National Museum of Brazil|accessdate=4 September 2018 |language=pt}}</ref> |- | | ''São João Nepomuceno'' | [[Siderite]] | [[São João Nepomuceno]], Brazil | 1960 | {{convert|15.3|kg|lb|abbr=on}} | <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.museunacional.ufrj.br/dir/exposicoes/geologia/geo022.html|title=São João Napomuceno|publisher=National Museum of Brazil|accessdate=4 September 2018 |language=pt}}</ref> |}
