[[File:Hall of Supreme Harmony 2018. Forbidden City.jpg|thumb|Hall of Supreme Harmony]]
The '''Hall of Central Harmony''' ({{zh|c=中和殿|p=Zhōng Hé Diàn}}) is one of the three halls of the Outer Court of the [[Forbidden City]], in [[Beijing]], China, along with the [[Hall of Supreme Harmony]] and [[Hall of Preserving Harmony]]. It is smaller than the other two halls, and is square in shape. It was used by the Emperor to prepare and rest before and during ceremonies.<ref name="DPM Zhonghedian"> {{cite web|url=http://www.dpm.org.cn/China/phoweb/BuildingPage/1/B484.htm|title=中和殿 (Hall of Central Harmony)|accessdate=2007-07-25|author=The Palace Museum|authorlink=|coauthors=|date=|year=|month=|format=|work=|publisher=|pages=|language=Chinese|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070530064123/http://www.dpm.org.cn/China/phoweb/BuildingPage/1/B484.htm|archivedate=2007-05-30|quote=|deadurl=yes|df=}}</ref>

