{{About|the publishing imprint|the 1979 film|Série noire (film)|the 1984 French TV series|Série noire (1984 TV series)|the 2014 Quebecois TV series|Série noire (2014 TV series)}} {{Infobox publisher | image = | parent = [[Éditions Gallimard]] | status = | founded = 1945 | founder = [[Marcel Duhamel]] | successor = | country = [[France]] | headquarters = [[Paris]] | distribution = | keypeople = | publications = [[Book]]s | topics = | genre = [[crime fiction]] | imprints = | revenue = | numemployees = | url = {{URL|http://www.gallimard.fr}} | traded as = }}
'''''Série noire''''' is a [[France|French]] [[publishing]] [[imprint (trade name)|imprint]], founded in 1945 by [[Marcel Duhamel]]. It has released a [[Collection (publishing)|collection]] of [[crime fiction]] of the [[hardboiled|hardboiled detective thrillers]] variety published by [[Gallimard]].
[[Anglosphere|Anglo-American]] literature forms the bulk of their collection: it features especially [[Raymond Chandler]], [[Dashiell Hammett]], [[Horace McCoy]], [[William R. Burnett]], [[Evan Hunter|Ed McBain]], [[Chester Himes]], [[Lou Cameron]], [[Jim Thompson (writer)|Jim Thompson]], [[James Hadley Chase|Rene Brabazon Raymond]] (under his pseudonym James Hadley Chase) and Peter Cheney. Books from the series were adapted into episodes on the 1984 television series [[Série noire (TV series)|of the same name]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.lexpress.fr/culture/livre/quel-polar-litteraire-choisir-sur-petit-ecran_898458.html |title=Quel polar littéraire choisir sur petit écran? |last1=Liger |first1=Baptiste |date=11 June 2010 |work=[[L'Express (France)|L'Express]] |language=French |accessdate=30 November 2014}}</ref>
This name became a generic term for works of detective, and is considered having inspired the French critic [[Nino Frank]] to create in 1946 the phrase [[Film noir]], which describes [[cinema of the United States|Hollywood]] [[Crime film|crime dramas]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.crimeculture.com/Contents/1945-70.htm|title=1945-70|publisher=Crimeculture.com|accessdate=30 November 2014|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150309034524/http://www.crimeculture.com/Contents/1945-70.htm|archivedate=9 March 2015|df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.commentfaiton.com/fiche/voir/9582/comment-definir-le-film-noir|title=Comment définir le film noir ?|work=commentfaiton.com|accessdate=30 November 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kdbuzz.com/?le-film-noir|title=Le Film Noir|publisher=Kdbuzz.com|accessdate=30 November 2014}}</ref>
In common parlance, today, the term also means a series of dramatic events with similarities, or affecting the same victims.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lepoint.fr/monde/fukushima-la-serie-noire-continue-03-10-2013-1738518_24.php|title=Fukushima : la série noire continue|author=Le Point, magazine|work=Le Point.fr|accessdate=30 November 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.marianne.net/Serie-noire-chez-JP-Morgan_a232318.html|title=Série noire chez JP Morgan|author=Adrien Francius|work=Marianne|accessdate=30 November 2014}}</ref>
