{{italic title}}
'''''The English Schoole-Maister: Teaching all his schollers, the order of distinct reading, and true writing our English tongue''''' is a [[dictionary]] compiled by [[Edmund Coote]], former Headmaster of [[King Edward VI School, Bury St Edmunds|King Edward VI School]], Bury St Edmunds, and first published in [[London]] in 1596. At least 40 editions were published between its first publication and the end of the 17th century.<ref name=Fenton>{{cite book|last=Fenton|first=Mary C.|title=Milton's Places of Hope: Spiritual And Political Connections of Hope With Land|year=2006|publisher=Ashgate Publishing|isbn=9780754657682|page=104}}</ref>

It went through several editions, with later editions having slightly different subtitles.

The publishing of the book most likely lead to him losing his job as headmaster.

