==Production==
A second season was ordered prior to the season one premiere. Filming for the second season began in February 2016; its story took place four years after that of the first season.

On 14 September 2016, producer Claude Chelli confirmed that ''Versailles'' had been renewed for a third season, which would begin filming in April 2017.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Sitbon|first1=Prescilia|title=C. CHELLI (CAPA Drama) : «Versailles saison 3 devrait entrer en tournage en avril 2017»|website= média+|url=http://www.lemediaplus.com/c-chelli-capa-drama-versailles-saison-3-entrer-tournage-avril-2017/|language=fr-FR|date=14 September 2016}}</ref> On 11 May 2017, the official Instagram account of [[Vaux-le-Vicomte|Château de Vaux-le-Vicomte]] published pictures of the ongoing shoot of the third season.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BT9ixozlQ6T/?taken-by=chateauvlv|title=Instagram post by Château de Vaux-le-Vicomte • May 11, 2017 at 6:10pm UTC|website=Instagram}}</ref> On 17 April 2018, ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]'' reported that the third season of ''Versailles'' would be its last.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2018/tv/global/canal-plus-fabrice-de-la-patelliere-versailles-3-1202745797/|title=Canal Plus’ Fabrice de La Patelliere on ''Versailles'' 3, What’s Next|first=Elsa|last=Keslassy|date=7 April 2018|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|accessdate=22 April 2018}}</ref>

==Broadcast==
''Versailles'' premiered on 16 November 2015 on [[Canal+]] in France and on [[Super Channel (Canada)|Super Channel]] in Canada, in May 2016 on [[BBC Two]] in Britain, and on 1 October 2016 on [[Ovation (U.S. TV channel)|Ovation]] in the U.S. [[The Movie Network]] gave early access to all of season 2 in October 2016, prior to its 2017 broadcast dates.<ref>{{cite web|title=Versailles|url=http://www.themovienetwork.ca/versailles|accessdate=3 April 2018 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161023041744/http://www.themovienetwork.ca/versailles|archivedate=23 October 2016}}</ref> The series stayed on the English-language Super Channel until May 2016<ref>{{cite web|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160520052433/http://www.superchannel.ca/collection/1/series|title=Series - Super Channel|date=20 May 2016|publisher=}}</ref> but was gone by December 2016,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161222014708/http://www.superchannel.ca/collection/1/series|title=Series - Super Channel|date=22 December 2016|publisher=}}</ref> after TMN had made season 2 available early. The French version of Super Channel is keeping the show available until 8 November 2020. [[Citytv|City]] aired the first six episodes of season 1 from January 4 to February 25.<ref>{{cite web|title=Versailles|url=https://www.citytv.com/toronto/shows/versailles/|publisher=Citytv.com|language=en-CA}}</ref>

The second season premiered on 27 March 2017 in France,<ref name="express" /> and aired from 21 April 2017 in Britain.<ref name="express">{{cite web|last=Kettley|first=Sebastian|title=When does Versailles season 2 start? BBC release date, cast, trailer, and more|url=http://www.express.co.uk/showbiz/tv-radio/775604/Versailles-season-2-when-start-BBC-release-date-cast-trailer-where-to-watch-Netflix-iTunes|website=[[Daily Express]]|publisher=[[Northern & Shell]]|accessdate=3 April 2017|date=31 March 2017}}</ref> At some point after the first season concluded, Super Channel lost the Canadian broadcast rights to the series.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://allarcoentertainment.zendesk.com/hc/en-us/articles/220384427-What-happened-to-Versailles-|title=What Happened to ''Versailles''?|date=3 June 2016|publisher=[[Super Channel (Canada)|Super Channel]]|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161116101314/https://allarcoentertainment.zendesk.com/hc/en-us/articles/220384427-What-happened-to-Versailles-|archivedate=16 November 2016}}</ref> Subsequently, [[The Movie Network]] picked up those rights and began airing reruns of the first season.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.themovienetwork.ca/versailles|title=The Movie Network - Series - Versailles|website=The Movie Network}}</ref>{{Better source|reason=Citation is The Movie Network's company website; there must be more objective sources for this.|date=April 2017}}

=== Filming locations ===
{{unreferenced section|date=July 2018}}
In addition to the [[Palace of Versailles]], many other palaces and chateaux were filmed for the depiction of the unfinished Versailles, including:
* The [[Château de Champs-sur-Marne]] gardens
* The [[Château de Janvry]]
* The [http://www.chateaudelesigny.com Château of Lésigny]
* The [[Château de Maisons-Laffitte]] (pictured below)
* The [[Château de Pierrefonds]] (pictured below) used as the castle preuses room
* The [[Château de Sceaux]]
* [[Vaux-le-Vicomte]] (pictured below)
* The Château of Vigny
* The [[commune]] of [[Rambouillet]]

